  "prompt": "If I live in NYC but work on Long Island do I have to pay city income tax?",
  "response": "Yes, if you live in New York City, you are required to pay New York City resident income tax, regardless of where you work. New York City's income tax is determined by your residency within the city rather than where your employment is located. Therefore, if your primary residence is in New York City, you will need to pay city income tax.",
